.TH "ubifs_write_node" 9 "ubifs_write_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_write_node \- write node to the media.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_write_node
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int lnum "  ","
.BI "int offs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "buf" 12
the node to write
.IP "len" 12
node length
.IP "lnum" 12
logical eraseblock number
.IP "offs" 12
offset within the logical eraseblock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function automatically fills node magic number, assigns sequence
number, and calculates node CRC checksum. The length of the \fIbuf\fP buffer has
to be aligned to the minimal I/O unit size. This function automatically
appends padding node and padding bytes if needed. Returns zero in case of
success and a negative error code in case of failure.
